# React Development

## Overview

This rule provides guidelines for React development.

## Key Guidelines

### Code Style

- Follow consistent naming conventions
- Use meaningful variable and function names
- Write clear, self-documenting code
- Follow React-specific idioms and conventions

### Best Practices

- Handle errors appropriately
- Write tests for new functionality
- Document complex business logic
- Use functional components with hooks, implement proper state management,
  optimize re-renders

### Performance

- Optimize for readability first
- Profile before optimizing
- Use appropriate data structures
- Consider memory usage and efficiency

### Security

- Sanitize user inputs, use CSP headers, validate props, avoid XSS vulnerabilities

